Dayaw Season 10 - Episode 2: Teofilo Garcia (Passing the Hat)   Teofilo Garcia was awarded the distinction of Gawad sa Manlilikha ng Bayan in 2012 for his work as maker of tabungaw. This hat he has devoted his life to creating is a symbol of how agriculture and ecology combine to create an object both beautiful and functional.   His life’s work now is to pass on his knowledge to young Abra-enos. He works closely with the teachers of San Quintin National High School, all whose firm understanding of Teofilo’s process, have contributed to the success of this techno-transfer program.

WATCH: Senate probe into the fatal hazing of UST student Horacio Castillo III  Here are the highlights:  - Gordon: Fraternities do not teach the members to lose their moral compass.  - Gordon to Solano: Assuming you survive this, may sasali pa kaya sa frat niyo na sirang-sira na ang prinsipyo?  - Solano: I was supposed to tell all, but since multiple charges were filed against me, I think I should invoke my right.   - Divina: Hazing should be completely banned. But initiation that does not cause physical and physiological harm to neophytes must be allowed.  - Sen. Drilon underscores need to examine Anti-Hazing Law: Current law allows hazing so long as frat notifies the school.  - Acting Prosecutor General admits inquest proceeding not proper because Solano voluntarily surrendered.  - Robinos, another member of Aegis Jvris Fraternity, said he did not undergo hazing   - Solano admits he was also subjected to hazing when he was recruited by the Aegis Jvris Fraternity  - Esmaquel: I have only attended 2 fraternity affairs since my admission to the Bar. As a founder, I was shocked.  - Atty: Paterno Esmaquel, one of the founders of Aegis Jvris says he came to know of the incident only through the newspaper.  - Sen. Sotto asks: Why bring Atio to CGH instead of UST Hospital? Solano answers: Frat members told me to follow them to CGH  - Solano: I administered CPR when I didn't hear a pulse.   - Solano: During first call, I was not told why I have to come. In the second call, I was only told that someone collapsed.  - Solano said he received a message Saturday morning from one of the frat members to come to the library; but he said he refused to come right away.  - Solano: Hindi ko po kilala si Atio. Hindi na po ako enrolled sa UST Civil Law.  - Poe asks Solano: Bakit ka nagsinungaling noong umpisa, bakit mo binawi ito?  - MPD: There was no cellphone recovered from Atio; his parents say many personal items were missing.  - MPD: When Atio's case was reported, we were not aware that he was a hazing victim.  - Divina: I have made a plea for those involved in Castillo's death to surrender.  - Divina: I took a leave from Aegis Jvris fraternity 8 years ago.  - UST Civil Law Dean Nilo Divina: I am a member but not a founder of Aegis Jvris.
